abstract: There is a window now to restore America’s credibility and bring more stability to the Middle East.

headline: Recycling in America Is a Mess. A New Bill Could Clean It Up.
abstract: As programs shutter and plastic use rises in the pandemic, a New York bill to get manufacturers to pick up the recycling tab could offer a solution.

headline: How Biden’s Climate Ambitions Could Shift America’s Global Footprint
abstract: Serious efforts to address global warming might mean big changes for America’s trade, foreign relations and even defense strategy.

headline: Can You Wear Floral on Your Buzz Cut?
abstract: The intricate art of hair tattooing reimagines the buzz cut as a blank canvas.

headline: The Reality Behind Biden’s Plan to Legalize 11 Million Immigrants
abstract: The proposal for a path to citizenship for undocumented residents has been called “the boldest immigration agenda any administration has put forward in generations.” But is it possible?

headline: Truckers Shun U.K. Ports to Avoid Brexit Red Tape
abstract: British ports expected gridlock after post-Brexit trade rules began on Jan. 1. Instead, some are nearly empty as truckers stay away, reluctant to spend hours waiting for newly required export documents.

headline: Living In ... Mahwah, N.J.
abstract: As one resident said of this Bergen County township, ‘The magic is the parkland, and how close it is to the city.’ Also, there’s a ski slope.

headline: No More Lies. My Grandfather Was a Nazi.
abstract: In Lithuania, he was celebrated as a hero. But we can’t move on until we admit what he really did.

headline: New Yorkers Can’t Find Parking. For Bikes.
abstract: The uptick in cycling during the pandemic has shined a light on the problem.

headline: Why Are Farmers Protesting in India?
abstract: Thousands of protesters, many driving tractors, took to the streets of New Delhi on Tuesday. Who are they, and what do they want?

headline: Why Are U.S. Coronavirus Cases Falling? And Will the Trend Last?
abstract: With vaccinations underway, and as multiple new coronavirus variants begin to spread, we check in on the state of the pandemic.

headline: A Populist Leader Kicks Off a Culture War, Starting in Museums
abstract: Slovenia’s government has replaced the directors of major institutions. But it says “run-of-the-mill artists really have nothing to complain about.”

headline: Russia’s Economic Slump Erodes Consensus That Shielded Putin
abstract: The rally-around-the-flag effect of President Vladimir V. Putin’s assertive foreign policy known as the Crimea consensus is unraveling with the economy.

headline: Australia locks down a whole city after finding a single new coronavirus case.
abstract: Australian officials abruptly locked down the city of Perth in Western Australia for five days, after one person tested positive there for the coronavirus — a security guard at a quarantine hotel. The state of Western Australia had gone nearly ten months without any sign of community transmission.

headline: Black and Latino New Yorkers Trail White Residents in Vaccine Rollout
abstract: Data showed that while 24% of city residents are Black, only 11% of vaccine recipients were. White New Yorkers received a disproportionate share of the shots.

headline: New York City postpones vaccine appointments as a snowstorm approaches.
abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio of New York announced on Sunday that vaccine appointments scheduled to take place in the city on Monday would be postponed because of a looming winter storm that is expected to dump up to 16 inches of snow on the region.

headline: Militants Storm Hotel in Somali Capital and Blasts Rock Area
abstract: The authorities said an evacuation operation was still underway at the Afrik Hotel, with reports of at least two dead and 11 injured. A  militant group, the Shabab, was believed to be behind the attack.

headline: Not Yet Desperate, Japan and South Korea Plod Toward Vaccinations
abstract: The slower pace gives the East Asian countries a chance to learn from mistakes elsewhere but also poses risks as more contagious and perhaps deadlier variants of the virus emerge.

headline: The Pop Star Wants to Be an Olympian
abstract: Cody Simpson has been a singer, a dancer, an actor and an author. Now, with support from Michael Phelps and Ian Thorpe, he is resurrecting a childhood swimming dream.

headline: N.Y.C. Facing ‘Profound Disparity’ in Covid Vaccinations, Mayor Says
abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio said data on the city’s vaccine rollout showed Black and Latino New Yorkers being vaccinated at starkly lower rates than white residents, who have gotten a disproportionate share of the shots.
